143
00:06:49,440 --> 00:06:51,670
That would be tragic
after all they've been through.

144
00:06:51,839 --> 00:06:53,431
I would cry like it was my own breakup.

145
00:06:53,599 --> 00:06:55,157
-Yeah.
-I don't think I could handle it.

146
00:06:55,359 --> 00:06:57,919
Whatever path these two choose,
I want them to end up together.

147
00:06:58,079 --> 00:07:00,388
GALECKI: Yeah.
-I want them to end up married, I really do.

148
00:07:00,559 --> 00:07:02,515
That's like my dream for these characters.

149
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:05,399
And lthink-- We deserve that
because we haven't played it like that.

150
00:07:05,559 --> 00:07:07,914
Like, it's gone back and forth,
we've broken up, we've--

151
00:07:08,079 --> 00:07:09,273
There's been so many things.

152
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:12,637
-Yeah, the characters have earned it.
-Yeah. It's not like, "Oh, that's typical."

153
00:07:12,799 --> 00:07:15,677
If they walk away after
all this empty-handed, good Lord.

154
00:07:15,840 --> 00:07:17,273
I would cry my eyes out. I would die.

155
00:07:17,439 --> 00:07:19,669
