For me, I think--

188
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:15,671
This is not hard to pull off
because I adore Jim.

189
00:09:15,879 --> 00:09:20,634
I think that this Amy character
is completely enamored with Sheldon...

190
00:09:20,839 --> 00:09:23,637
...and I think in the sweetest
and most reasonable way.

191
00:09:23,839 --> 00:09:26,194
lfeel like I'm being strangled
by a boa constrictor.

192
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:31,150
Why'd you stop?

193
00:09:31,879 --> 00:09:35,235
You know, from all the kind of, like, funny
comments about his sallow complexion...

194
00:09:35,440 --> 00:09:37,476
-...and, you know, his hunched over--
-Watch it.

195
00:09:37,680 --> 00:09:40,319
Ha-ha-ha.
I didn't write that. They did.

196
00:09:40,519 --> 00:09:43,670
Um, no, but I think for all his quirks,
I think they're all forgivable.

197
00:09:43,880 --> 00:09:45,871
Think about it, Sheldon.
Your personality quirks...

198
00:09:46,079 --> 00:09:47,671
...which others find abhorrent
or rage-inducing...

199
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:48,909
...I find cute as a button.

200
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:52,471
-She doesn't have a lot of other options.
-Well....

201
00:09:52,679 --> 00:09:55,671
But still, there's something very attractive
about their relationship.

202
00:09:55,880 --> 00:10:00,908
In many ways, it is one of the most stable
relationships on the show...

203
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:04,078
...certainly until Wolowitz and Bernadette
got married...

204
00:10:04,280 --> 00:10:06,191
...which I think solidifies things.

205
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:08,675
Well, who knows in today's society?
No. Um, but....

206
00:10:08,880 --> 00:10:10,108
There's a real understanding...

207
00:10:10,280 --> 00:10:12,919
...between the two of them
of where they stand.

208
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:15,680
You know, when l have afeeling, I know it.

209
00:10:15,880 --> 00:10:17,233
And trains? Love them.

210
00:10:18,680 --> 00:10:20,636
Hand-holding? Not a fan.

211
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:25,834
